The Russians are owed BILLIONS of dollars by iraq.  Russia isn't in great economic shape and if the government of hussien falls, they might never see it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxaenneax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xaen Neax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 489<br> <font color=#333333>(9/12/02 11:32:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=929.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/philipv1/small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WAR DECLARED!</span><hr size=1> Agree. Bush basically said to the UN that they need to enforce the sanctions. Iraq needs to pass 16 more checks before the sanctions can be lifted. If they pull anything, complain, push inspectors away then <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> there will be a new ruling party put in place in Iraq</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Majority of the UN agree'd for a change. They are going to give Iraq one very last chance to grin and bear it, and if they decide to play games, or pull any stunts, then their government will be forcefully disbanded without hesitation. After Afganistan, they would be fools to do otherwise. All in all, it was a very good, and firm speech. It needs to be done. Leaving the pot to boil will only bring the world something worse than 9/11 ten years from now. People who think Saddam will just forget about getting his ass handed to him by the world 10 years ago are kidding themselves. Iraq says the USA's statements have no proof. That is not the issue, the issue is that the UN and USA needs to PROVE them. Taking their word for it is not good enough for anyone.<br>
