<br>
The “Gathering Danger” line reminds me of the book Winston Churchill wrote,” The Gathering Storm” I believe it was named. In which he tried to get his message across that Hitler could not be trusted to follow any deals or treaties. Neville Chamberlain disagreed. The result was WWII. Sadam would obviously be Hitler, I wonder who best represents Chamberlain... Koffe Anon maybe.<br>
<br>
On a different note why the hell is the US President asking permission from the UN? I’ll bet anyone here that using a UN imposed sanction as justification to attack Iraq is going to come back and bite the US in the ass. Most of the member nations in the UN do not have democratic governments. Despots and dictators run many of them. Many are Theocracies or Monarchies. Many of the leaders don’t give a damn about world peace; they only care about getting a few bucks in their pockets.<br>
<br>
