<br>
Can someone name one good thing the UN has ever accomplished? I mean something beyond providing a forum for debate. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uetanalhorrhammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Etana Lhorrhammer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/AFK No</span><br>  Posts: 344<br> <font color=#333333>(9/12/02 12:27:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=929.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.getinfo.net/douge/etana.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WAR DECLARED!</span><hr size=1> I think Bush has made a good point.  The UN has put up with Saddams lack of cooperation for what, 7-12 years?  He hasn't complied to most, if any, of the demands that the UN has made.  And these are basic reasonable demands... stop torturing people, account for the more than 600 political prisoners that are still missing, stop supporting terrorism, etc.  If the UN is going to work, then it has to back up those demands with force when necessary.  Give Iraq one more chance to comply (which frankly is more than is deserved at this point) or take action. <p><P>
